HEADWORD: Magnetomotor
<hw>Mag`net*o*mo"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A voltaic
series of two or more large plates, producing a great quantity of
electricity of low tension, and hence adapted to the exhibition of
electro-magnetic phenomena.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>magneton</ent>⟦br⟧
